qas.question: What does every cardinal priest not have?
What has not been expanded beyond the Roman pastoral clergy and Roman Curia?

plausible_answers.text: all administrative rights cardinals had with regard to their titular churches

qas.question: What did Pope Paul V abolish?

plausible_answers.text: the cardinal's name and coat of arms

qas.question: What is not still posted in the church after Pope Paul VI abolished all administrative rights?

plausible_answers.text: celebrate mass and preach there if convenient when they are in Rome.

qas.question: What are cardinals not expected to do?

context: While <b2_0>the cardinalate<b2_0/> has long been expanded beyond the Roman pastoral clergy and Roman Curia, every cardinal priest has <a0_0><b1_0>a titular church in Rome<b1_0/><a0_0/>, though they may be bishops or archbishops elsewhere, just as cardinal bishops are given one of the suburbicarian dioceses around Rome. Pope Paul VI abolished <b3_0>all administrative rights cardinals had with regard to their titular churches<b3_0/>, though <b4_0>the cardinal's name and coat of arms<b4_0/> are still posted in the church, and they are expected to <b5_0>celebrate mass and preach there if convenient when they are in Rome.
